<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LOUSISANA; 
</P>
<P>
27 CONCERT-GOERS HURT IN WINDSTORM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
High winds hurled debris and ripped down a stage where up to 10,000 people had 
gathered for an outdoor concert in Baton Rouge, La. 
</P>
<P>
At least 27 were injured on the grounds of the Centroplex, part of the city 
government building complex across the street from the Mississippi River levee. 
The sudden storm downed power lines and tree limbs across Baton Rouge, a police 
dispatcher said. In one neighborhood the bark from sycamore trees was literally 
ripped from the trunks and thrown onto the roofs of houses. About 25,000 people 
in New Orleans were without electricity for at least part of the evening, 
officials said. 
</P>
