<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO; 
</P>
<P>
SEIZED FISHING BOAT WILL BE SEARCHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Crews worked to unload fuel tanks on a 90-foot fishing boat seized in a drug 
raid off the coast in the Bay Area so the boat could be searched for hidden 
compartments, the Coast Guard said. No contraband was immediately found on the 
boat, which was seized off Half Moon Bay and towed to San Francisco after San 
Mateo County sheriff's deputies spotted a suspected drug-smuggling operation 
along the coast, the Coast Guard said. 
</P>
<P>
Twelve men -- seven on shore and five aboard the vessel -- were arrested, and 
federal and state officials combed a 20-mile stretch of coastline for drugs 
they suspect were dumped from the trawler. Five pounds of marijuana was seized 
on shore near Pescadero, about 30 miles south of San Francisco, deputies said. 
The arrests and seizure came after deputies spotted several people on 
California 1 throwing something from a bridge, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
