<HEADLINE>
<P>
AFFANDI; INDONESIA'S TOP EXPRESSIONIST PAINTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Affandi, 83, an Expressionist painter whose works were exhibited worldwide. 
Considered Indonesia's foremost Expressionist, Affandi began painting 
professionally in 1938. "Ibu" ("Mother") was a masterpiece of his realistic 
works before he turned to Expressionism. 
</P>
<P>
"Self Portrait" is another famous work among the 4,000 paintings he created. In 
1948, he traveled to India and later became a guest lecturer at the East-West 
Center in Hawaii. His works were exhibited in London, Paris, Rome, Rio de 
Janeiro and The Hague. In 1956, he exhibited his works in the United States 
under an Asia Foundation grant. President Suharto had given him Indonesia's 
highest award for artistic achievements while "Fire to Live" was a 1982 Swedish 
documentary on his life. Near Jakarta on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
