<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARX LEWIS; VETERAN LABOR ORGANIZER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marx Lewis, 93, veteran labor organizer. Lewis earned a law degree from the 
American University in 1924 but never practiced, choosing to become an 
organizer for the Cap and Millinery Workers Union. 
</P>
<P>
A socialist in his youth, he held several labor positions and helped organize 
the Liberal Party of New York. He served in the Administration of Republican 
New York City Mayor Fiorello LaGuardia in the 1930s and 1940s and later became 
a Republican. On Tuesday in Silver Spring, Md. 
</P>
