<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Munch Exhibit Opens: The tormented inner life of Norwegian artist Edvard Munch, 
who once said that "my pictures are my diaries," is laid bare in a new 
exhibition of his prints that opened Sunday at the National Gallery of Art in 
Washington. The show's 94 prints were assembled from the holdings of Sarah and 
Lionel Epstein, who plan to give their entire collection of about 200 Munch 
woodcuts, lithographs and other graphic works to the museum. The exhibit will 
travel later this year to Los Angeles. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
