<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CBS Joins CNN: In a cost-saving experiment that may be tried elsewhere 
overseas, Cable News Network and CBS News will share a bureau and satellite 
equipment in Berlin. The test will start in mid-June and is "a limited 
experiment," in which the two organizations will maintain separate news 
correspondents and producers. The Berlin bureau arrangement marks the second 
deal between CBS and cable tycoon Ted Turner, who unsuccessfully tried to buy 
CBS in 1986. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
