<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
254 TRUCKS CITED IN SURPRISE CHP CHECK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol said it gave tickets to 74% of the trucks pulled 
over in surprise inspections last week. 
</P>
<P>
The Highway Patrol inspected 342 trucks on heavily traveled California 118 near 
Tierra Rejada Road in Moorpark on Wednesday and Thursday, a CHP spokeswoman 
said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities said tickets -- primarily for brake, suspension, steering and other 
mechanical violations -- were given to 254 trucks. The CHP ordered 141 of the 
vehicles out of service. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities estimate that about 1,200 truckers use the highway between Moorpark 
and Somis daily. The CHP chose California 118 as a checkpoint site because many 
truckers use the highway to avoid the Conejo Weigh Station on the Ventura 
Freeway, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The CHP holds about eight surprise inspections per year at that location, the 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
