<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR ARRESTED IN BURGLARY OF LIQUOR STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four burglary suspects were arrested Sunday after a resident saw a break-in at 
an El Cajon liquor store and called police. 
</P>
<P>
When Officer Michelle Hales arrived at the store in the 400 block of Jamacha 
Road about 4 a.m., she saw four people run to a pickup and speed away, a 
spokeswoman for the El Cajon Police Department said. 
</P>
<P>
A 10-minute chase by Hales and other officers followed, ending when the 
suspects crashed the truck into a guardrail at the end of El Jardin Court in El 
Cajon, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspects ran from the vehicle, but were captured and taken into custody. 
During the pursuit, a drawer containing cash and a large quantity of 
cigarettes, with a combined value of $20,000, were thrown from the vehicle, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspects were booked into County Jail on suspicion of burglary. They were 
identified as John Huggins, 39; David Jason Brown, 34; Krystal Arlene Durio, 
25, and Lisa Williams, 29, all of San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the suspects may be linked to a series of other burglaries in El 
Cajon earlier this month. 
</P>
