</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GOING. . . Orange County people are travelers, much more so than their L.A. 
Basin neighbors. . . . A 1988 study showed they were 28% more likely to visit 
foreign parts and a whopping 68% more likely to travel the United States. . . . 
About 43% of county adults had traveled abroad between 1986 and 1988, 
contrasted with only about 34% for the greater L.A. area. 
</P>
<P>
FOREIGN VACATIONS 
</P>
<P>
43.4% of O.C. adults took foreign trips, including to Mexico, between 1986 and 
1988. Of those: 
</P>
<P>
73.8% took 1 or 2 trips 
</P>
<P>
21.9% took 3 to 6 trips 
</P>
<P>
4.3% took 7 or more trips 
</P>
