<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kathie Bozanich 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Today is Memorial Day, a day set aside to remember those who have died in wars. 
The following will be closed in observance of the holiday: 
</P>
<P>
All county, state and federal offices. 
</P>
<P>
All schools, including colleges and universities. 
</P>
<P>
County, state and federal courthouses. 
</P>
<P>
City and county libraries. 
</P>
<P>
Banks and savings and loans. 
</P>
<P>
All city offices. 
</P>
<P>
Mail: All post offices will be closed today, and mail deposited in mailboxes 
today will be picked up according to the posted holiday schedule. There will be 
no mail delivery today. 
</P>
<P>
Trash: There will be no trash pickup by city or county refuse workers today. 
Trash pickups will be a day late in all areas, with the exception of Fullerton 
and Orange. Residents in those cities are asked to put out their trash on their 
regularly scheduled day, except those with regular Monday pickups, who should 
put out their trash on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Buses: Orange County Transit District buses will run on the holiday/Sunday 
schedule today. There will be no dial-a-ride or car-pool services available. 
</P>
</TEXT>
