<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE COMMUNITY COLLEGE BASEBALL; 
</P>
<P>
L.A. HARBOR BEATS CHABOT, GAINS FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
L.A. Harbor College held off a ninth-inning rally to defeat Chabot, 10-9, 
Sunday to advance to today's championship of the state community college 
baseball tournament at UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Harbor led, 10-5, to start the ninth, when Chabot's Corey Quinn led off with a 
double. 
</P>
<P>
He scored on a single by Brian Thompson. A single by Barney Dion chased Harbor 
starter Pat Ahearne, who was replaced by Chico Limas. 
</P>
<P>
Aaron Ledesma lined a three-run home run off the scoreboard to cut the lead to 
10-9. Limas got Chad Burns to fly out for the first out before being replaced 
by John Ingram, who got the game's final two outs. 
</P>
<P>
Chabot (43-11) also reached today's championship game by defeating Santa Rosa, 
18-6, later Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Chabot and Harbor meet again today at 11, with Chabot having to win twice for 
the title. A second game would follow, if necessary. Harbor (50-5) last won the 
state title in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
The ninth-inning home run Sunday was the 10th consecutive time Ledesma had 
reached base safely in the tournament. His streak grew to 11 when he walked in 
his first at-bat against Santa Rosa (32-19), but he flied out in the third 
inning. Ledesma is nine for 12 with two home runs, three doubles, 10 runs 
scored and 10 RBIs in three tournament games. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Rosa defeated Riverside, 11-5, earlier Sunday to eliminate the Tigers 
(32-17) from the tournament. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
